channel.description:
Welcome to my channel!  Here I document some of the major unaddressed issues that San Francisco is facing, namely drugs, homelessness, and insufficient mental health services.  San Francisco is a small city, 7x7 miles, with a population of around 600,000 (although on any given day it may hold up to 4 million people due to tourism.)  10,000 of this population are homeless.  That is huge, that is 1 and 2/3rds percent.  60% of the methamphetamine consumed in the US comes through San Francisco.  Methamphetamine has gotten so cheap that it is starting to replace crack cocaine as the primary street drug used by the homeless.

Comments people have left:
Lee, I love your channel. You present the most realistic depictions of San Francisco I've seen on the internet, and this is coming from me born and raised out here. Keep uploading more!

Just wanted to say thanks for risking not only yourself your equipment, these are the videos that should be seen by the people of sf... (text limit)
